description:
When people 'die of old age', they really die from age-related diseases like heart issues, cancer, or respiratory diseases. Sadly, most of them cant be cured today, but lets assume for a minute that they could be in the near future. As soon as an organ fails, we could replace it and live on for as long as we wanted, right?
